    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="594"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-09-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 576.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose copy of a dispatch from our
                    consul-general at Habana transmitting correspondence from Bridat, Montros &amp;
                    Co., agents of the American tobacco manufacturing firm, Seidenberg &amp; Co.,
                    and from <pb facs="0782" n="688" xml:id="pg_688"/> Bauriedel &amp; Co., agents
                    of other American importing houses, claiming that they have not been allowed, in
                    accordance with the understanding indicated in your telegram of May 25 last, to
                    export tobacco purchased before the prohibitory decree of the Governor-General
                    was issued.</p>
                <p>You will bring these cases to the attention of the Government of Spain, and urge
                    that the arrangement reached shall be adhered to by the Cuban authorities.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
